      "writtenOn": "2021-03-11T02:17:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I removed this function.\n\n--------------\nThe field name is named with \"parent\" in the proto, and I prefer to have proto parsing functions named with the proto field.\n\nI\u0027d argue that artifacts.ParseParentID() shouldn\u0027t be exposed outside. ParentID is an internal representation of the parent key in Spanner, and business logic deals with the proto level representation of the parent. Just like how Invocations.ID encapsulates the transformation between the Spanner and proto representation of the invocation ID, we could add artifact.Parent. Then, there will be only one \"Parent\" and we can avoid naming confusion.\n\ni.e.,\n```\npackage artifact\ntype Parent string\nfunc (p Parent) ToSpanner() interface { ... }\nfunc (p Parent) FromProto() interface { ... }\n```",
