      "writtenOn": "2021-03-04T22:35:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: consider moving this into the L182. There is no need to pass invState from one goroutine to another: the goroutine that got invState can do the whole job.\n\ni essentially propose in the L155 comment. It seems right now we have to goroutines that only do reads and put the data into a common variables, and then main goroutine do the actual checks. My proposal is that individual goroutines do the checks too, so that variables are *more local*, but also checks would happen concurrently\n\nre *more local*: currently the reader of L199 has read another function body to verify if the key format matches. If that happens in one function, it is more local.\n\nin other words, the only common thing between these two checks if that they both use a txn. Most of their code has little to do with each other.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 194,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 196,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "ce363dbd65396e64e80999d31d6b54ce5618fb18",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
