        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-11T02:17:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done.\n\nI tried to avoid performing hash calculations inside the Spanner transaction. The transaction would create a write lock on the invocation and artifact rows, if previously reported already.\n\nThat said, I realized that it was unnecessary optimization, because\n1) The invocation row is updated only when it is finalized, by one worker.\n2) Most artifacts wouldn\u0027t have rows in Spanner, when this API is called.\n3) Also, we never modify Artifact rows, once created.",
      "parentUuid": "2ca38dc2_2615eb0c",
