      "side": 1,
      "message": "Removed L213, and I\u0027d like to keep it w/o a helper function.\n\nIf I added hash() to artifactCreationRequest{}, then it would have to check for thread-safety and cache staleness. (or add a warning comment)\ne.g.,\n```\n// This will return stale Hash if a.data is ever updated after the first time of this function call.\n// Don\u0027t do the following.\n//\n// a \u003d artifactCreationRequest{testID: 123}\n// a.hash()\n// a.data \u003d \"the content\"\nfunc (a *artifactCreationRequest) hash() {\n  a.hashLock.Lock() // or atomic.LoadPointer(), if we assume that we never change a.data.\n  defer a.hashLock.Lock()\n  if a.cachedHash \u003d\u003d \"\" {\n    a.cachedHash \u003d hash\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe code looks too adhoc and I don\u0027t see much benefit of extracting this to a small helper function with the receiver, because its usage is too limited.\n\nI could just add it to a small helper function, as Chan suggested, but now, there is only one place calling it and # of lines is 2. I will add a helper function, if there are more needs.",
